{"id": "EUVD-2022-55036", "enisaUuid": "e10d8d4c-0104-325a-ae56-d3488c158a57", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nkernel/resource: fix kfree() of bootmem memory again\n\nSince commit ebff7d8f270d (\"mem hotunplug: fix kfree() of bootmem\nmemory\"), we could get a resource allocated during boot via\nalloc_resource().  And it's required to release the resource using\nfree_resource().  Howerver, many people use kfree directly which will\nresult in kernel BUG.  In order to fix this without fixing every call\nsite, just leak a couple of bytes in such corner case.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T01:55:37", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T19:27:48", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a9e88c2618d228d7a4e7e515cf30dc0d0d813f27", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d7faa04a44a0c37ac3d222fa8e0bdcbfcee9c0c8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ab86020070999e758ce2e60c4348f20bf7ddba56", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0cbcc92917c5de80f15c24d033566539ad696892", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49190", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3379a60f6bb4afcd9c456e340ac525ae649d3ce7", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/05/msg00030.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49190"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0c81948d-b9e2-3d77-a340-ce9a4a05c45e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3.10"}, {"id": "29f042dc-c8c1-3728-aed2-fb591ff43b01", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.33"}, {"id": "46f6d755-5827-3c34-a701-b6953ca0a722", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.237"}, {"id": "6364a913-88f3-33a0-8d50-eda896437ccd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "7618778a-bfaa-37dd-b0f8-f5cbde366a35", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ebff7d8f270d045338d9f4796014f4db429a17f9 <a9e88c2618d228d7a4e7e515cf30dc0d0d813f27"}, {"id": "802bfbdf-01dc-37da-adbc-a9e7c4f74cf7", "product